\begin_layout BeginFrame
The Story Behind “When Harry Met Iannis”
\end_layout

\begin_layout Quotation
Iannis Xenakis passed away on February 4, 2001.
 When he arrived in Heaven, he sought out his mentor, Olivier Messiaen.
 Messiaen said, “Iannis, there’s someone here I want you to meet.” The two
 walked over to a small sidewalk cafe, and there sat Harry Partch.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Quotation
And so from this fanciful meeting in Heaven, “When Harry Met Iannis” was
 born.
 From Partch, the piece inherits the 43-tone just scale, tuned to G = 392
 Hz.
 Also from Partch, the piece inherits the need to build instruments to play
 in the Partch scale.
 The harmonies in “When Harry Met Iannis” are derived from the Tonality
 Diamond.
\end_layout

