\begin_layout BeginFrame
Final Chord Generation
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
One of the Identities is chosen at random as the “root” of the chord
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
This “root” is placed in the octave between 1/1 and 2/1 for an Otonality
 and between 1/2 and 1/1 for a Utonality
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
The rest of the pitches in the chord are placed in the octave up from the
 root for an Otonality and down from the root for a Utonality
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
The whole chord is then transposed according to the octave multiplier
\end_layout

